reviewText: This long-time comedienne, now gone unfortunately, is one of the funniest of her genre, and I have seen such artists all the way back to Bea Lillie (I'm in my 80s...).  If you also happen to be a classical music lover, it becomes superb.  If you are also familiar with Wagner's 4-opera "Ring of the Nibelungen" as I am though I never much liked it, then her famous routine explaining it is funny beyonds words and can be watched over and over again without losing its charm and ability to evoke laughter.
Title: N/A

reviewText: ANNA RUSSEL  (The first Farewell Concert)I had requested "Anna Russell Sings! Again? with John Coveart at the piano.Recorded in New York Town Hall  1953This DVD is a much older version of a tired entertainer, recorded in a small theatre in Baltimore Museum.  No back grownd, small audience.  Really on the last throws of her career. Not entertaining,  poor sound reproduction.I give it one star only because of remembering Anna Russell twenty-five years younger. This DVD belongs IN a museum.

reviewText: I have a couple CDs of her routines and wanted to see her "live." This satisfies that desire, but it's what she says that interests us, and the CDs are sufficient.
